HEADWORD: Archæopteryx
<hw>Ar`ch⟦ae⟧*op"te*ryx</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'archai^os</grk> ancient + <grk>pte`ryx</grk> wing.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A fossil bird, of the Jurassic period,
remarkable for having a long tapering tail of many vertebr⟦ae⟧ with
feathers along each side, and jaws armed with teeth, with other
reptilian characteristics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

